=== Auxiliary verb ===

'''would'''

#Expressing something that might have happened if something else had happened first. 
#:''We would be warmer if you hadn't opened the window!'' 
#Expressing something that might happen later. 
#:''We sat on the bench, wondering if the bus would be on late this time.''
#Expressing something that was planned or intended. 
#:''The waiter said he would be right back.'' 
#Expressing something that happened often or commonly. 
#:''In the winters we would sit by the hole on the frozen lake and fish for hours.'' 
#Expressing a request. 
#:''Would you please turn off the TV?'' 

